e the importance of Capito and his colleagues in providing advice in matters concerning the churches in southern Germany and Switzerland, but also regarding the evangelicals in neighbouring France.Milton Kooistra’s annotation provides historical context by identifying classical, patristic, and biblical "ations as well as persons and places. Continuing in the tradition of rigorous scholarship established in Volume 1 and Volume 2, this volume provides crucial details on the evolution of Capito’s thought and its contribution to the Reformation movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHumanistszEuropevCorrespondence. 0aReformationzEuropevCorrespondence. 0aScholarszEuropevCorrespondence. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aKooistra, Milton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRummel, Erika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144262487040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442624870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442624870/original  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles